const String wtp = 'The planting scheme has to take into consideration the size and growth habit of the species.';
const String wtp1 = 'All these components together with bio-degrading agents like white-rot, brown-rot, group of stain fungi and insects like borer and termites make bamboo prone to attack and thus fast decay fast. It is estimated that more than 40% of bamboo is being destroyed due to these biological agents during use and storing in un-treated conditions.';
const String wtp2 = 'The durability of bamboo can be enhanced by adopting preservation methods with or without chemicals.However, from scientific point of view and field experience, it has proved that application of chemicals in the preservation methods enhances the life of bamboo many times than without chemicals.';
const String wtp3 = 'The precautionary measures for increasing the life of harvested bamboo poles by adopting preservation methods can be applied right from the time of harvest.';
const String wtp4 = 'Storage of Harvested Culms';
const String wtp5 = 'Proper storage of harvested culms is an important aspect as negligence on this part can cause great losses. Whenever bamboo is stored, it should be ensured that the culms do not up-take any additional moisture either by rain on by ground contact. Culms left on the ground open to rain are prone to infestation by fungi, beetles etc. Further, to avoid cracking by sun exposure, the culm should be preferably placed under cover for a period of 6 to 12 weeks depending on the season.';
const String wtp6 = 'There are many preservation techniques both as Traditional Methods as well as Chemical Methods.';
const String mt = 'TRADITIONAL METHOD';
const String mt1 = 'CHEMICAL METHOD';
const String tm = 'SELF CULM CURING';
const String tm1 = 'In this process the selected culm is cut at the base and left for a few days within the clump which provide leaning support for a few days. The bottom of the harvested culm, should preferably, should not touch the ground and may be placed over a stone, etc. When the leaves, branches etc turn yellowish brown, the culms are removed and transported to the storage site. It may be noted that the culm weight while removing from the clump is reduced because of loss of water due to continuous transpiration by the leaves and also the starch content is reduced.';
const String tm2 = 'WATER CURING';
const String tm3 = 'This is a common practice. The freshly cut culms are put either into running water or stagnant water like pond for 1 to 3 months. The affect of this treatment is better if the nodal walls are ruptured.However, if the storage under water is prolonged, the culm gives bad odour and may lead to staining. This treatment improves resistant to borers and some stain fungi. Culms or slivers to be used for handicraft products may also be boiled in fresh water for 30 to 60 minutes which gives good results.';
const String tm4 = 'SMOKING CURING';
const String tm5 = 'The best form of treatment or the preservation technique is the aged old technique of smoking. The people of the North East from time immemorial used to store the bamboo and cane products on top of the fire place. Due to gradually and continuous heat the insects or borers which attacks the bamboo products could not withstand the heat, if done for a period of a month the product are well treated and preserved. On top of that, an oily fluid is secreted which gives a shining effect.';
const String tm6 = 'GAS METHOD';
const String tm7 = 'Gas method of treatment for faster method by covering the bamboo with plastic sheet and gas being injected.';
const String tm8 = 'SMOKING METHOD';
const String tm9 = 'The Japanese method of curing by slow heating.';
const String cm = 'SPRAYING METHOD';
const String cm1 = 'In this method, chemicals/insecticides are mixed and dissolved in water and either sprayed on the stacked bamboos or the bamboos are put into the solution for about 30 minutes. The solutions can be made from various chemicals. But, considering the rural environment and expertise in handling such chemicals, a dose of Borax with 6–8% concentration or Borax and Boric acid (1.5:1) with 5% concentration is recommended. The stacked bamboo should not be kept in touch with the ground directly and not exposed to rain.';
const String cm2 = 'DIPPING METHOD';
const String cm3 = 'In this process, the poles or slivers to be used for making handicraft products or furniture, mats, etc are recommended as this process is more effective than the previous one. If slivers/strips are to be used, they may be bundled together before dipping. The solution may be made from Borax : Boric acid in proportion to 1.5:1 with concentration of about 5%. The time of dipping depends upon requirement and end use. However, as a thumb rule, 30 minutes dipping is will give some protection.';
const String cm4 = 'BORIC AND BORAX';
const String cm5 = 'The most common one is the boric acid and borax powder. The method of mixing depends from process to process. For smaller bamboo or strips, it is done in an ordinary bucket, for longer bamboo to the drum etc.';
const String cm6 = 'BOUCHERIE PROCESS';
const String cm7 = 'This is a widely recognized process which has been recently adopted on commercial scale. The basal end of the freshly felled bamboo is attached to a hose-pipe fixed to a reservoir of water-borne wood preservative solution (Boric+ Borax +water solution). This process is suitable for freshly felled green bamboo with branches and leaves intact. In this process, the preservative is pushed through the bamboo by gravity from a container placed at a height. The penetration and absorption of the preservative depends upon several factors such as concentration of solution, treatment time, nature of chemicals used, dimensions of the bamboo, its age and moisture content.';
const String cm8 = 'CREOSOTE OIL';
const String cm9 = 'For whole bamboo specially used for housing building and also for scaffolding jobs, treatment are done by infusion of chemical like creosote mixed with diesel. This method is popular in the construction sector. Should not be used for exposed bamboo parts recommended for poles only if injected properly.';
const String cm10 = 'Injection Of Castrol Oil';
